<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-17 20:55:29 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE>  Galaxy 3, Rapids 0 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	PASADENA, Calif. (AP) -- Greg Vanney and Cobi Jones scored  
second-half goals Sunday as the Los Angeles Galaxy, who played a 
man down for 72 minutes, beat the Colorado Rapids 3-0 in the 
opening game of the best-of-3 MLS Western Conference semifinals. 
</P>
<P>
	Los Angeles was forced to play with just 10 players after  
midfielder Simon Elliott was ejected after receiving his second 
yellow card. His cleats hit Colorado defender Marcelo Balboa's 
thigh during an attempted tackle. 
</P>
<P>
	Elliott, who received his first yellow card from referee Marcel  
Yonan in the sixth minute for fouling defender David Vaudreuil from 
behind, will also be suspended for Game 2 under league rules. 
</P>
<P>
	Ezra Hendrickson scored in the eighth minute and Vanney made it  
2-0 with a penalty-kick goal in the 52nd minute. The Galaxy were 
awarded the penalty kick after Rapids defender Chris Martinez 
pulled down midfielder Mauricio Cienfuegos by the jersey in the 
penalty area. 
</P>
<P>
	Jones scored in the 57th minute, tapping in a loose ball after  
goalkeeper Ian Feuer deflected Clint Mathis' cross but the Rapids 
were unable to clear the ball away. 
</P>
<P>
	Kevin Hartman made seven saves for the shutout as Colorado's  
offensive woes continued. The Rapids were shut out in their final 
five regular season matches and were held scoreless for 499 
consecutive minutes, an MLS record. 
</P>
<P>
	Colorado led 14-12 in shots and 8-6 in shots on goal. Feuer made  
three saves before a Rose Bowl crowd announced at 16,307. 
</P>
<P>
	Game 2 will be played Sunday in Denver. A third game, if  
necessary, would be played Oct. 27 at the Rose Bowl. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW19991017.0007 </DOCNO>
