<HEADLINE> Karl Malone To Miss Four More Games </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SALT LAKE CITY (AP) -- Utah Jazz forward Karl Malone is expected  
to miss the next four preseason games due to a lower back strain. 
</P>
<P>
	The 36-year-old Malone will miss Monday's exhibition game at the  
Delta Center against the New York Knicks, and is not expected to 
make this week's trip to Nashville, Indianapolis and Lexington, Ky. 
The Jazz have two games against the Boston Celtics and one against 
the Indiana Pacers. 
</P>
<P>
	Malone's status for the final two preseason games against the  
Pacers in Salt Lake City and against the Los Angeles Lkers in 
Anaheim, has not been determined. 
</P>
<P>
	Utah is scheduled to open the season on Nov. 2 against the  
Lakers. 
</P>
<P>
	``Karl is in real good shape; he always is,'' said coach Jerry  
Sloan. ``But he'll need to play some basketball. I don't think 
there's any question about that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Malone, who signed a four-year, $67 million contract during the  
offseason, first felt his back tighten almost two weeks ago. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
