<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-17 10:30:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Jets Bench Mirer for Lucas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	EAST RUTHERFORD, N.J. (AP) -- Rick Mirer was benched as New York  
Jets quarterback Sunday by coach Bill Parcells, with Ray Lucas 
making his first NFL start. 
</P>
<P>
	Parcells hinted during the week he might make a change at the  
position, which has been in flux since Vinny Testaverde tore his 
Achilles' tendon in the season opener. Mirer, acquired Aug. 20, was 
slow to learn the offense and was coming off a weak performance 
last Monday night against Jacksonville. He was demoted to third 
string, behind punter Tom Tupa, for the game with Indianapolis. 
</P>
<P>
	Lucas, in his third NFL season, generally has played on special  
teams. He received about half of the snaps in practice during the 
week. Lucas has appeared in nine games at quarterback for the Jets, 
but only sporadically. He has not played quarterback this year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
