<HEADLINE> Kieser Wins Detroit Marathon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DETROIT (AP) -- Fred Kieser won the Detroit Free Press/Flagstar  
Bank International Marathon on Sunday, beating his nearest 
competitor by more than 4 1/2 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	Kieser, who is from Lakewood, Ohio, covered the course in 2  
hours, 18 minutes, 27 seconds, finishing ahead of three Kenyans. 
Cleophas Boor finished second at 2:22:59, followed by Reuben 
Chesang (2:24:57), and John Kipkoskei (2:28:37). Paul Aufdemberge 
of Redford, Mich., finished fifth at 2:30:49. 
</P>
<P>
	Russian Irina Khramova won the women's division with a time of  
2:43:58. Leslie Carson of Canada finished 27 seconds back. 
</P>
<P>
	Krige Schabort of Cedartown, Ga., easily won the wheelchair  
division with a time of 1:41:36, beating Tony Iniguez of Aurora, 
Ohio, by more than 16 minutes. 
</P>
<P>
	The course took a new route this year, starting and finishing at  
Tiger Stadium and including a run through the Windsor Tunnel and 
over the Ambassador Bridge. 
  	   	
</P>
