<HEADLINE> St. Mary's Appoints Hoops Coach </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ST. MARY'S CITY, Md. (AP) -- St. Mary's College has hired Alfred  
Johnson as interim men's basketball coach to replace Othell Wilson, 
who was placed on leave after his arrest on rape charges, the 
school announced Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	Johnson spent the past two seasons as an assistant coach at  
Tuskegee University. Since 1990, he has served as an assistant 
coach at Alabama State, Tennessee State, Elizabeth City State and 
Manor Junior College in Jenkintown, Pa. 
</P>
<P>
	Wilson, who played with Ralph Sampson at Virginia, was accused  
last month of abducting a 22-year-old woman and raping her at his 
apartment. Wilson played on Final Four teams in 1981 and 1984 
before moving on to the NBA, where he played with Sacramento and 
Golden State. 
</P>
<P>
	The 38-year-old Wilson had promoted to head coach at St. Mary's  
in August. 
</P>
