<HEADLINE> Williams Beats Hingis in Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ZURICH, Switzerland (AP) -- Venus Williams routed Martina Hingis  
6-3, 6-4 to win the Swisscom Challenge on Sunday, denying Hingis a 
chance to capture her first title in her home country. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams defeated the world's top-ranked player for her sixth  
title this season. She did not lose a set all tournament. 
</P>
<P>
	This was Williams' second consecutive victory over Hingis. She  
beat her in the Grand Slam Cup semifinals two weeks ago. 
</P>
<P>
	Hingis last defeated Williams in the U.S. Open in September.  
Hingis won that semifinal before losing the final to Venus's 
sister, Serena. 
</P>
<P>
	Williams lost to Lindsay Davenport last year in the finals of  
this tournament. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
