<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lexicon Wins Ancient Title Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ARCADIA, Calif. (AP) -- Lexicon took the lead at the start and  
then put away the bid of 4-5 favorite Kona Gold in midstretch to 
score a two-length victory Sunday in Oak Tree's $207,500 Ancient 
Title Breeders' Cup Handicap at Santa Anita. 
</P>
<P>
	Lexicon posted a stakes record, covering six furlongs in 1:07  
4-5. 
</P>
<P>
	The resounding performance earned the 4-year-old colt, ridden by  
Ken Desormeaux and trained by Richard Mandella, a trip to the Nov. 
6 Breeder's Cup Sprint at Gulfstream Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Kona Gold, who finished third in last year's Breeders' Cup  
Sprint, made a determined effort through the stretch under Alex 
Solis. They got alongside Lexicon nearing the sixteenth pole, but 
the latter pulled clear in the final yards. 
</P>
<P>
	Regal Thunder was third, another six lengths back. Eary Pioneer,  
Emailit, Young At Heart, Another Star and Kid Katab completed the 
order of finish. 
</P>
<P>
	Lexicon carried 116 pounds and paid $8.40, $3.80 and $2.80. Kona  
Gold, the high weight at 120 pounds, paid $2.80 and $2.20, while 
Regal Thunder returned $2.40 to show. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
