<DOCNO> APW19991017.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-10-17 17:00:11 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Clinton Golfs Alone in Rain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WASHINGTON (AP) -- Under a steady drizzle, the nation's first  
golfer had the course to himself Sunday, playing a full 18 holes 
into the early evening. 
</P>
<P>
	President Clinton left the White House on short notice to play  
speedy game without partners under the instruction of one of the 
Army and Navy Country Club's golf pros. 
</P>
<P>
	Clinton wore a burgundy sweatshirt and a white sports hat that  
was dripping wet by 7 p.m., when he stepped into his limousine for 
the short ride back to the White House. The White House press 
office refused to release his score. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
