<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Five Found Dead in Denver Car </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DENVER (AP) -- Three women and two men were killed when the car  
they were in apparently missed a stop sign at the bottom of a steep 
hill and came to rest upside down in a river south of downtown, 
police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Detective Virginia Lopez said police received a call shortly  
after 9 a.m. from someone who reported seeing the car. One of the 
officers who responded immediately jumped into the Platte River and 
tried to break the car's windows to free the victims, but he was 
unsuccessful, Ms. Lopez said. 
</P>
<P>
	It appeared the victims had been dead for some time.  
</P>
<P>
	``They could have been there anywhere between last night and 9  
this morning,'' she said. 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. Lopez said there were no cans or bottles inside the car to  
indicate whether alcohol was a factor in the accident, but she said 
tests would be conducted on the victims. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
