<HEADLINE> Monarch's Maze Wins Jamaica Handicap </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Monarch's Maze, the favorite in a field of  
non-stakes winners, finished 1 1/4 lengths in front of Killer Joe on 
Sunday to win the 50th running of the $150,000, Grade II Jamaica 
Handicap at Belmont Park. 
</P>
<P>
	Monarch's Maze, who finished second in the Grade III Saranac at  
Saratoga in his previous start, covered 1 1/8 miles on a good turf 
course in 1:51:3. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Joe Bravo, Monarch's Maze earned $90,000 for Live Oak  
Plantation and paid $5, $3.20 and $2.30. It was the third win in 
nine starts this year for the Florida-bred. 
</P>
<P>
	Killer Joe finished a half-length in front of Monkey Puzzle in  
the field of eight 3-year-olds. 
</P>
<P>
	Killer Joe paid $4.80 and $2.70, while Monkey Puzzle was $2.40  
to show. 
  	   	
