<HEADLINE> Maple Leafs 2, Blackhawks 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	CHICAGO (AP) -- Jonas Hoglund and Yanic Perreault each scored a  
goal, while Glenn Healy stopped 25 of 26 shots as the Toronto Maple 
Leafs held on for a 2-1 win over the Chicago Blackhawks on Friday 
night. 
</P>
<P>
	Josef Marha's power-play goal with 7:05 remaining in the third  
period spoiled Healy's bid for a 12th career NHL shutout. But even 
though the Blackhawks came on to test the Toronto goaltender in the 
game's final minutes, Chicago remained winless at 0-3-2-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Toronto, skating without injured star center Mats Sundin,  
improved to 5-2-0-0. 
</P>
<P>
	Healy, a back-up netminder to Curtis Joseph, was making only his  
second start of the season. 
</P>
<P>
	Hoglund's deflection during a Toronto power play at 12:44 of the  
first period opened the scoring. Stationed in the slot, he 
redirected Alexander Karpovtsev's shot from the right point past 
Chicago goaltender Jocelyn Thibault. 
</P>
<P>
	Perreault converted a two-on-one break with Hoglund at 16:07 of  
the second period to extend the Maple Leafs' lead to 2-0. Carrying 
the puck down right wing, Perreault faked a pass to Hoglund, then 
fired himself and beat Thibault with a high, glove-side shot. 
</P>
<P>
	Marha ruined Healy's shutout bid during a Chicago power play  
with 7:05 left in regulation. Marha's shot, the Blackhawks' 22nd 
shot on goal of the game, from the right circle deflected off 
Toronto defenseman Cory Cross and sailed over Healy's glove. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
