<CATEGORY> weather </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> The Nation's Weather </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	The Carolinas soaked in rain from Hurricane Irene on Sunday. The  
Northeast and New England saw rain and clouds as well, while much 
of the rest of the nation was fair and dry. 
</P>
<P>
	Clouds from Irene trailed well across east Pennsylvania and New  
Jersey through northeast and central Florida. 
</P>
<P>
	A frontal boundary system stretched from the Northeast through  
lower Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Skies were mostly cloudy from upper New England through upper  
Minnesota, through the Ohio Valley to Arkansas, Oklahoma, most of 
Texas, and New Mexico. 
</P>
<P>
	Snow showers, mixed with rain or sleet in spots, fell in middle  
and upper New Mexico through northwest Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	Elsewhere, a disturbance moving into Montana brought clouds.  
</P>
<P>
	The rest of the nation was dry and fair to partly cloudy,  
including the western Appalachians to the central Gulf States, the 
remaining upper Plains and the remaining western states. 
</P>
<P>
	Temperatures across the Lower 48 ranged from a low of 4 in  
Leadville, Colo., to an early-afternoon high of 86 in Marathon, 
Fla. With the wind chill, it felt like minus 14 in Leadville, Colo. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
